race.comment: ARTIE LADY (5) is a former Victorian who won her Maiden here second-up, quickly finding for Matt Dunn.  Has an awkward barrier, but she's sure to keep improving and is well-placed to take the next step. DO IT FOR YOU (2) resumes and will be much more competitive than the form line suggests. Will race over further but has won fresh and over this course/distance. Owns an easy trial win here, and a bold return is likely. STEEL RAIN (1) needed the first up outing and can show more with that under the belt. He's having his first full campaign for the Grisedale yard following the switch from a top Sydney stable. Maps well and has a 2kg claim in easier. SHOOT THE DIVA (4) has pieces of form that would see her around the mark. ALABAMA GIRL (7) tries hard as well, but needs to find plenty to be winning.
